gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 125, Magic 113
gameRecap.excerpt: The 76ers defeated the Magic, 125-113. Joel Embiid (32 points, 13 rebounds, seven assists) and Tyrese Maxey (28 points, three assists) combined for 60 points for the 76ers, with Kelly Oubre Jr. adding 21 points and nine rebounds in the victory. Paolo Banchero tallied 22 points, season-high 15 rebounds, and seven assists for the Magic in the losing effort. The 76ers have won seven games in a row and improve to 46-35, while the Magic fall to 46-35.
